track_notes: Park at the Trailhead alongside the dirt road.  Nice  rocky trail with a few steep sections.  The summit looks imposing as you approach but there is a trail to the top!  A very small amount of exposed scrambling right at the top, so you may want to set up below in the Activation Zone if you dont feel safe.  The summit has spectacular views and had a tree that I used to strap my mast.
track_title: 2555 Peak from the West via National Trail

track_notes: Curtis Saddle Trailhead to San Juan Lookout parking via National Trail, then San Juan Lookout to summit via Alta Trail.  Be careful that there are a few areas to easily take the wrong turn.  1st one about midway between the TH and San Juan Lookout.  Be sure to stay straight - do not take a right or left.  2nd one is right at San Juan.  The rest is pretty easy to follow.  Also watch out for snakes.
